Overview
========

XtalOpt searches for the global minimum of a crystal structure's
PES using a evolutionary algorithm. It is implemented as an extension
to the Avogadro molecular editor and licensed under the GPL v2 or later.


Installation
============

See INSTALL.


License
=======

GPL v2 or later. See COPYING.


Files
=====
Interface (dialog, tabs, etc):
  -- src/xtalopt/ui/*

Genetic operator implementation:
  -- src/xtalopt/genetic.*

Debugging:
  -- src/generic/bt.*

Local optimizer interfaces:
  -- src/xtalopt/optimizers/pwscf.*
  -- src/xtalopt/optimizers/gulp.*
  -- src/xtalopt/optimizers/vasp.*
  -- src/generic/optimizer.*

Event loop for testing/benchmarking purposes
  -- src/testing/xtalopttest.*

Evolutionary algoritm "engine":
  -- src/xtalopt/xtalopt.*

Avogadro extension interface:
  -- src/extension.*

Queuing and job control:
  -- src/generic/queuemanager.*

Structure management:
  -- src/generic/tracker.*

Spacegroup identification:
  -- src/spglib/debug.*
  -- src/spglib/pointgroup.*
  -- src/spglib/spglib.*
  -- src/spglib/symmetry_kpoint.*
  -- src/spglib/spacegroup_database.*
  -- src/spglib/primitive.*
  -- src/spglib/cell.*
  -- src/spglib/bravais_art.*
  -- src/spglib/symmetry.*
  -- src/spglib/spacegroup_data.*
  -- src/spglib/spacegroup.*
  -- src/spglib/bravais.*
  -- src/spglib/mathfunc.h

Crystal object data structure:
  -- src/generic/structure.*
  -- src/generic/xtal.*
